{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_116","type":"agent_message","text":"I verified the required GraalVM exactly:\n\n```text\nnative-image 25.0.3 2026-04-21\nGraalVM Runtime Environment Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+9.1\nSubstrate VM Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+9.1\n```\n\nThen I reproduced the requested failure with `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.aesh:readline:3.2`. The failing test is still `org_aesh.readline.AbstractPtyInnerReflectionFileDescriptorCreatorTest`, and the runtime error is `UnsatisfiedLinkError: org.jline.nativ.CLibrary$Termios.init()V`.\n\nI tried the obvious metadata-side repairs and also aligned the test with the existing JLine native-access flags, but neither changed the failure, so I reverted all of those edits. The workspace is unchanged.\n\nThe key finding is that this is not specific to `org.aesh:readline:3.2`: under the same GraalVM and mode, `org.jline:jline-terminal-jni:3.30.7` also fails with the same `CLibrary$Termios.init()` error. I also confirmed that the extracted `libjlinenative.so` does contain the expected JNI symbol and that the equivalent JVM test passes. That points to a broader JLine JNI/native-image runtime issue with this GraalVM setup, not a narrow missing metadata entry for `org.aesh:readline:3.2`.\n\nIf you want, I can continue on the broader fix path instead of the org.aesh-only metadata path."}}
